 the Hawaiian Ola ideaSupport Hawaii’s environment and economy by empowering local farmers producing organic, responsibly grown crops







 







 OUR PHILOSOPHYWhat Responsibly Grown Means To Us WORK WITH THE LANDUse the natural design of the land, ecology, and climate to farm with natureUSE NON-TOXIC METHODSFarm without using chemicals that are toxic for humans or the environmentPLANT THE RIGHT CROPSGrow plants that thrive naturally and compliment their growing environmentSOURCE LOCALLYSource farming inputs like plant starts and amendments locally when possibleSTART WITH GOOD SOILGrowing healthy, nutrient-rich soil is the first step to growing healthy food cropsTHINK LONG TERMInvest in sustainable growing for the future using permaculture techniquesUSE A HOLISTIC APPROACHConsider whole systems and the true impacts (externalities) of farmingALIGN FOOD AND VALUESGrow food in a way that upholds farmer and community stakeholder values  







 Goals For 2020Source 100% of our ingredients from certified organic Hawaiian farmsCreate a demand for one thousand acres of organic Hawaiian farmland and increase total harvested organic crops in Hawaii by 30%Bring two million dollars in new annual Ag income to over sixty small Hawaiian farmsImpact For HawaiiIncreased Hawaiian crop production without increased use of toxic chemicals on the landNew income and farming opportunities for responsible Hawaiian growersNew economic activity for Hawaii coming from organic value added exportsMore healthy, locally grown food and beverage alternatives to imported products for Hawaii shoppers




 our planEncourage growers who farm responsibly by providing them with the support they need to launch and sustain successful farms and by giving them a reliable market to sell their crops.







Organic Farm SupportEmpowering Farmers: Providing growers with key agricultural resources needed to responsibly grow more organic crops in HawaiiOur aim is to create new and lasting farming career opportunities for people in Hawaii by assisting farmers with farm planning, responsible Ag education, and by providing resources, such as locally sourced growing inputs and healthy plant starts.We’re promoting good custodianship of the Hawaiian environment through education on farming and food production techniques that are aligned with our Responsible Growing philosophy. We see value in empowering farmers who consider externalities (the true costs of food production for all stakeholders) to grow more good food!Healthy Products BrandCreating Demand: Bringing responsibly grown Hawaiian crops to market in healthy products made by the Hawaiian Ola brandWe give Hawaiian farmers an equitable market to sell their responsibly grown crops by turning their goods into healthy, value-added consumer products and bringing them to market under the Hawaiian Ola brand. Our brand’s success encourages producers to grow more organic food for local and off-island markets, which supports a more resilient, self-reliant Ag economy in Hawaii.Hawaiian Ola believes in taking an Ag-informed approach to developing products. We collaborate closely with our farm partners to help them make informed decisions about what to grow. They, in turn, help us develop healthy products from ingredients that make good growing sense for farmers. 



























